cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.FL

This paper deals with the application of OCATA to model-checking MITL formulas against timed automata. The paper introduces a new semantics for OCATA and proposes a new algorithm to translate an MITL formula into a timed automaton. These topics are related to logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and formal languages (cs.FL).
